  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The following diagram 20 shows the discriminative and generative models of handwritten digits [14].Note, by constructing a line in the data space, the discriminative model aims to distinguish between handwritten 0 s and 1 s. If the line is drawn correctly, it can discriminate between 0 s and 1 s without ever having to represent the precise placement of the instances on either side of the line in the data space.",
    "The generative model, on the other hand, attempts to generate acceptable 1 s and 0 s by producing digits that closely resemble their actual counterparts in the data space.",
    "The distribution throughout the entire data space must be modeled.",
    "Autoencoder:The AE is a generative method that can be suitable for extracting the features and reducing the size with the same number of input and output units.",
    "These input and output layers are connected with one or more hidden layers."
  ],
